{
  "stem": "8842.2",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And very, very prominent rabbis came out from that area.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So Slabodka is not just-- it was not a very outgoing place, and not too many rich people lived there, but the yeshiva was one of the best in the world, and incredible.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We had to find a place, so most of the Lithuanians that lived there took over the Jewish homes in the other side of the river, and this is how we exchanged homes with the Lithuanians.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Most of the Lithuanians that lived there were very, very poor, and now they moved into lovely builded homes that the Jewish people-- they were very-- not very, very rich, but very good-- in good shape.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Jewish people had very-- they were, all of them, businesspeople and teachers and music people.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And you-- it was a very-- Lithuanian Jews were known as very learned people, and I would say elite of the Jewish European people.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It was a very modern and outgoing and sophisticated country, Lithuania.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "As bad as it was, the Lithuanians, but the Jews were very sophisticated, and living that way, too.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "We didn't have many Hasidim there, but religious people of sophistication was in them.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 6 SECONDS] It was 19-- that was 1941.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "We all moved in in, I think it was in-- at this point, August that we were all put into the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It was closed up with wires all around us.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And there were Lithuanians and German-- Lithuanian police and German army, always watching us.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We couldn't have big and wide apartments or homes, so they pushed us in, sometimes two or three families in one house.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "My parents found a tiny, little house for the six of us.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And right away, the first week came-- they call it [INAUDIBLE]-- action.",
      "word_count": 12
    }
  ],
